<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB4FFEEFF1CF9B44C1CFDDE" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB4FFEEFF1CF9B44D11FE7E" blockId="5.[113,766,1634,1946]" lastBlockId="5.[801,1453,279,559]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFF1CF9B44989F988" box="[151,235,1634,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Notes. –</emphasis>
No original material of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB4FFEEFD8BF9B44BADF988" box="[512,719,1634,1658]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFD8BF9B44BADF988" box="[512,719,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Polypodium acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been located in G-PREL. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB4FFEEFE11F9544B24F968" author="BURMAN" box="[410,582,1665,1690]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768)</bibRefCitation>
referred only to three pre-Linnaean polynomial names and an illustration (PLUKENET, 1694: tab. 285, fig. 1). One of these polynomial names referred to Burman’s father work: “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFDC1F9344B89F90B" box="[586,747,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Burm. Zeyl. 98</emphasis>
”. Johannes Burman’s 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFEB4F8D44B69F8EB" box="[319,523,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Thesaurus zeylanicus</emphasis>
, published in 1737, was based mainly on a Paul Hermann herbarium from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB4FFEEFDF1F8F44BA5F8CB" box="[634,711,1826,1850]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
. This herbarium is bound in a folio volume now kept in BIF-CEYL with Benjamin Delessert’s personal library (see 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB4FFEEFD0FF8B449C4F868" author="LOURTEIG" firstAuthor="LOURTEIG" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" pagination="23 - 33" part="15" refId="ref9722" refString="LOURTEIG, A. (1966). L'herbier de Paul Hermann, base du Thesaurus zeylanicus de Johan Burman. Taxon 15: 23 - 33." title="L'herbier de Paul Hermann, base du Thesaurus zeylanicus de Johan Burman" type="journal article" year="1966">LOURTEIG, 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Page 152 of this bound herbarium features a collection of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB4FFEEFCB6FEC14D60FEDE" box="[829,1026,279,303]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFCB6FEC14D60FEDE" box="[829,1026,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Polypodium acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, bearing a reference to the protologue as well as the name of the new species, both from N.L. Burman’s hand. This collection, representing original material, is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB4FFEEFC3DFEA14D75FE7E" box="[950,1047,375,399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFB4FFEEFBAEFEA14D04FE7E" box="[1061,1126,375,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,164,1889,1908]" captionTargetBox="[332,1278,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[332,1278,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. – Page 152 of Paul Hermann’s herbarium from Ceylon in BIF-CEYL with the lectotype of Polypodium acutum Burm. f. (upper specimen) and original material of Polypodium palustre Burm. f. (lower specimen). [© Bibliothèque de l’Institut de France, Paris]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5684542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5684542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB4FFEEFCCCFE414C1CFDDE" blockId="5.[801,1453,279,559]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">
The 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB4FFEEFCF5FE414A87FE5E" box="[894,997,407,431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">lectotype</typeStatus>
matches with sterile pinnae of the fern 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB4FFEEFCAAFE614AAFFE3E" box="[801,973,439,463]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Osmundaceae" genus="Osmunda" kingdom="Plantae" order="Osmundales" pageId="5" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regalis">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFCAAFE614AAFFE3E" box="[801,973,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Osmunda regalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, showing similar shape of pinnules and free venation. 
<location id="D437604FFFB4FFEEFC0FFE014AD3FE1E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:59418782FFB4FFEEFFFAFA7A4C1CFDDE:D437604FFFB4FFEEFC0FFE014AD3FE1E" box="[900,945,471,495]" country="Sri Lanka" county="Hermann" municipality="It" name="This" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">This</location>
species is widely cultivated and popularly known as ‘royal fern’. 
<collectingMunicipality id="3133ACEEFFB4FFEEFC24FE214AA3FDFF" box="[943,961,503,526]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">It</collectingMunicipality>
does not occur naturally in 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB4FFEEFB54FE214C25FDFE" box="[1247,1351,503,527]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB4FFEEFADEFE214A33FDDE" author="SLEDGE" firstAuthor="SLEDGE" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bull." pageId="5" pageNumber="98" pagination="9 - 11" part="36" refId="ref10235" refString="SLEDGE, W. A. (1981). The Ceylon Species of Osmunda. Kew Bull. 36: 9 - 11." title="The Ceylon Species of Osmunda" type="journal article" year="1981">SLEDGE, 1981</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB4FFEEFC06FDCE4A92FDDE" box="[909,1008,536,559]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">
<collectingCounty id="38364E18FFB4FFEEFC06FDCE4A92FDDE" box="[909,1008,536,559]" pageId="5" pageNumber="98">Hermann</collectingCounty>
</emphasis>
probably collected a cultivated plant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
